Module mesakit.map.ui.desktop
Package com.telenav.mesakit.map.ui.desktop.tiles

Class SlippyTile

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.mesakit.map.ui.desktop.tiles.SlippyTile
public class SlippyTile extends Object
A "slippy tile" is a rectangle defined by a zoom level and x, y coordinates in the grid of all tiles. You can get the bounds of a particular slippy tile like this: 
 var bounds = new SlippyTile()
     .withX(300)
     .withY(40)
     .withZoomLevel(ZoomLevel.forInteger(5))
     .bounds()

You can also find the slippy tile for a location like this: 

 var tile = new SlippyTile(CheckType.OSM, zoom, location)
Author:
jonathanl (shibo)
See Also:
"http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Slippy_map_tilenames"
